{
	"name": "Warp Perception",
	"type": "spell",
	"img": "icons/magic/control/hypnosis-mesmerism-eye.webp",
	"system": {
		"description": "<p><em><strong>Target:</strong> A number of Creatures equal to your Psionic Ability Modifier.</em></p><p>Perception is reality, and you have learned to alter the perceptions of entire groups of creatures at the same time, shifting their understanding of reality in one of the following ways. When you manifest this power, each target may make a Wisdom saving throw against the effect.</p><p><strong>Addition:</strong> Your targets perceive twice as much of something. If they are looking on a group of creatures, that group appears to have twice as many people in it, with any incongruities in space accounted for by distortion of the shared space. This effect only functions on discrete objects and not things like the digital printout of an object’s value, but would make a pile of credits appear to be twice as large.</p><p><strong>Subtraction:</strong> You remove a single entity or object from your target’s perception. Any investigation or perception check to locate the object, no matter how large or obvious, is made at disadvantage, and the subtracted creature or object may make stealth checks without cover or concealment. Examples include an allied creature or the Exit Door of a room. For objects, set the Investigation or Perception DC as equal to your Psionics saving throw DC.</p><p><strong>Creation:</strong> Your targets perceive an entity or object taking up to a 10ft cube of space. This entity or object cannot move from that location, though it can move within that space if it is smaller than 10ft on a side. If you choose, the creation may also make noises such as words or music, regardless of how inappropriate that would be for your creation. Example: A dog playing a jazz saxophone.</p><p>Any target which interacts with the addition or creation function of this power cannot use expertise on any skill check related to the illusion. This effect lasts for up to 1 minute so long as you maintain concentration.</p><h2>Augments:</h2><p><strong>Duration:</strong> +1 minute per Augment.</p><p><strong>Swap:</strong> Your targets perceive two entities or objects as being in opposite locations. For example you may cause them to perceive you as being one of their allies, and that ally as you. Directly interacting with either swapped entity or object triggers an immediate Wisdom saving throw to end the effect.</p><h2>Augments requiring two Psi Dice:</h2><p><strong>Additional Effect:</strong> You may simultaneously use two separate effects, such as Subtraction and Creation, rather than only one.</p><p><strong>Deletion:</strong> When you Subtract a creature or object from perception your targets become incapable of perceiving that creature or object whatsoever. Any perception or investigation check to locate the creature or object automatically fails and the creature or object cannot be attacked or interacted with by the targets. If a creature deleted in this way attacks a target that cannot perceive it, this power immediately ends for that target, alone.</p><p><strong>Expansion:</strong> Increase the range of this power by a factor of 10 for every 2 Augments, as well as the space a Creation can occupy.</p>",
